!        BEFORE SIMULATION:                                                                                             !
!        There is a _THEORY_ of method:                                                                                 !
!                  J. Phys. Soc. Jpn. 87, 063801 (2018) - https://journals.jps.jp/doi/abs/10.7566/JPSJ.87.063801        !
!        There is an _ALGORITHM_ of method and examples of simulations:                                                 !
!                  Yu.S.Nagornov, R.Akashi Physica A, 528, 121481 (2019) - https://doi.org/10.1016/j.physa.2019.121481  !
!                                                                                                                       !
!        CITATION:                                                                                                      !
!        --------                                                                                                       !
!        Publications making substantial use of AtomREM  or diagonalHESSIAN package for LAMMPS  			!
!	 or results of simulations should cite this software package and the following paper:				!
!        Yu.S.Nagornov, R.Akashi  "AtomREM: Non-empirical seeker of the minimum energy escape paths                     !
!                               on many-dimensional potential landscapes without coarse graining", arXiv:1907.13316     !
!                                                                                                                       !
!_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________!
!															!
!	CONTENT OF DIRECTORY:												!
!	- IN/ AND OUT/ folders contain the input and output files for 1 simulation for argon cluster with 7 atoms	! 
!									as an example of simulation			! 
!	- PATH_WAYS_7/ folder contain data of a lot of simulations for 							!
!							argon cluster with 7 atoms within several directories:		!
!			- RAW_DATA_OF_40_SIMULATIONS/	-   40 simulations are obtained in REACTION mode		!  
!			- SADDLE_POINTS/		-   the set of unique saddle points from 40 simulations		!
!			- TO_BOTH_SD/ 			-   the simlation with saddle point 				! 
!											connected to three stable state	!
!			- TO_OCTAHEDRON/ 		-   the simulation from pentagonal bipyramid to octahedron	!
!			- TO_TETRAHEDRON/ 		-   the simulation from pentagonal bipyramid to tetrahedron	!
!			- TO_TRIGONAL_BIPYRAMID/	-   the simulation from pentagonal bipyramid to bipyramid	!
!                                                                                                                       !
!                                                                                                                       !
!	The folder /PATH_WAYS_7/RAW_DATA_OF_40_SIMULATIONS/STRUCTURES/ contain the 40 initial atomic structures 	!
!	for 40 simulations, which were found by simulation in the mode "INITIALIZATION"					!
!                                                                                                                       !
!	The folder SADDLE_POINTS/ contain the data of analysis for 40 simulation, which allows to extract the 		! 
!	saddle points and it's connections to the stable structures. To visualize the data, please, use R or R studio 	!
!	to run R script "Unique saddles.R"!										!
!                                                                                                                       !
